overview: The user initiated a request to assess their existing sleep
  questionnaire application against a provided Statement of Work. The primary
  goal was to identify and plan for the implementation of a database to store
  questionnaire responses, an administrative dashboard for client access, and an
  authentication mechanism. The assistant conducted a thorough review of the
  codebase, pinpointing the absence of a dedicated response database, data
  retrieval capabilities (like CSV export), and any form of client-facing
  dashboard or authentication. Through clarifying questions, it was decided to
  proceed with a simple password-based authentication system and to integrate a
  comprehensive set of demographic fields. The resulting plan details the
  creation of a PostgreSQL database schema, new API endpoints for saving and
  retrieving responses, a lightweight authentication system, and the development
  of an admin dashboard with CSV export functionality. The plan also includes
  necessary updates to existing questionnaire forms and validation schemas,
  providing a clear roadmap for implementation.
